<HEADLINE>
FT  16 JUL 94 / World Commodities Prices: Spices
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Despite the holiday season, activity in the pepper market have been picking
up lately, reports Man Producten. White pepper prices rose considerably
during the week, mainly in the forward positions, because of the delayed
harvest in Indonesia and a very tight spot position in Europe and the US.
The spot price went to about USDollars 3,150 a tonne and July-August
shipment was quoted at Dollars 3,050 cif. The more distant positions were
somewhat discounted. Black pepper prices also developed a much firmer trend
as soon as fresh buying interest appeared. All origins are now extremely
reluctant to sell, as if the real statistical picture has become a lot
clearer. Spot black pepper grade 1 was quoted at Dollars 1,900 a tonne and
fair average quality at about Dollars 1,825, with very little supply
available in Europe.
</TEXT>
