Sir, Harrods Bank is and always has been owned by the department store,
Harrods Limited, contrary to your report of July 12 ('Harrods' new bank
manager').
Since 1991 the bank has been independently managed through a trustee, Law
Debenture Trust Corporation, but has continued to offer a full banking
service to our customers. The change followed the publication in 1990 of the
Department of Trade and Industry report into the takeover of the House of
Fraser, the validity of which we have never accepted and which we are
challenging before the European Court of Human rights.
