<HEADLINE>
FT  16 JUL 94 / Pounds 466,000 profit for electric chief
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By WILLIAM LEWIS and DAVID LASCELLES
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Mr James Smith, chairman of regional electricity company Eastern, has made a
profit of Pounds 466,867 by cashing in share options awarded to him after
privatisation.
It brings to more than Pounds 12m the profits made by directors of the UK's
privatised water and electricity companies exercising their share option
perks.
Many of the executives are sitting on substantial profits from share options
they have not yet exercised and also from options they have exercised but
have not yet sold.
On April 5 Mr Smith, who at privatisation earned a salary of Pounds 62,270,
exercised 121,107 share options. He immediately sold 60,554 shares at 6.69p
each and 60,553 the day after at 6.80p, to give him a total profit of Pounds
466,867. Three other Eastern directors recently exercised share options
bringing them a combined profit of Pounds 143,000. The company said that it
was 'a private matter for the directors whether they exercised the share
options'.
A spokesman said that 'in order to attract and retain senior executives of
the right calibre and degree of specialist talent Eastern has to be prepared
to offer a remuneration package which is comparable with the rest of
industry'.
Eastern's recently published annual report gives some details of directors'
share options but does not reveal the actual profit Mr Smith made. This
practice is in line with several other water and electricity company
reports.
Stock Exchange disclosures compiled for the Financial Times by The Inside
Track, an Edinburgh-based consultancy, reveal the actual gross profits made
by directors when exercising share options.
Mr Tony Coleman, group finance director of Yorkshire Electricity, made a
profit of Pounds 152,550 by exercising 61,957 options in April and then
selling on 45,000 shares. That left him with 16,957 shares which are
currently showing a paper profit of Pounds 49,854.
Water company directors have made total profits of about Pounds 4.5m by
exercising options and selling shares since January last year.
Cashing in, Page 8
