FT  16 JUL 94 / Ex-Nissan chief to appeal to Lords
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Former Nissan UK managing director Mr Michael Hunt was yesterday given leave
to appeal to the House of Lords against his conviction for involvement in a
Pounds 55m tax fraud.
The Court of Appeal, which rejected Mr Hunt's initial challenge in May,
certified that the case raised a point of law of general public importance
enabling a petition to the law lords for leave to appeal.
