<HEADLINE>
FT  16 JUL 94 / Finance and the Family: Goodbye to the account system - At a
Glance
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Britain's idiosyncratic system of two-week account periods for dealing in
equity shares ended yesterday. Under the account system all transactions
within the account period were aggregated and clients settled the net amount
due on settlement or account day. As from Monday Rolling Settlement takes
over.
