<TEXT>
Archer Daniels Midland, the US-based international agribusiness company,
reported fourth-quarter earnings of Dollars 138m, or 42 cents a share, up
from Dollars 124m, or 36 cents, in the same 1993 quarter.
Full-year net earnings were Dollars 484m, or Dollars 1.47 a share, compared
with Dollars 567m, or Dollars 1.66, after special tax credits, in fiscal
1993.
Sales data for the year and the quarter will only be released as part of
official filings to the Securities and Exchange Commission, the company
said.
ADM is one of the world's leading maize processors, and is also engaged in
flour milling and soyabean crushing. It is a primary producer of
high-fructose corn syrup.
