forecast, citing growing depreciation expenses. Many analysts, however, are
still forecasting a full-year figure close to MDollars 200m.
TRI's chairman and majority shareholder is Mr Datuk Tajudin Ramli, a Malay
businessman and protege of the influential former finance minister Mr Tun
Daim Zainuddin. TRI and MHS are near completion of a demerger exercise,
after which MHS will purchase a 32 per cent stake in Malaysian Airlines.
