<HEADLINE>
FT  15 JUL 94 / UK Company News: Furniture side helps Hampson to Pounds 4m
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By CAROLINE SOUTHEY
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
A surge in sales in the furniture division of Hampson Industries, the West
Bromwich-based diversified industrial group, contributed to a 75 per cent
rise in pre-tax profits from Pounds 2.42m, restated for FRS 3, to Pounds
4.23m in the year to March 31 1994.
The increase in profits was achieved after charges of Pounds 1.39m, which
included a goodwill write-off of Pounds 937,000 following the closure of
Clearway Aluminium, the only division in the company involved in the
construction industry.
Operating profits rose from Pounds 4.39m to Pounds 6.28m with continuing
operations up 34 per cent at Pounds 6.64m (Pounds 4.95m). Turnover advanced
to Pounds 91.5m (Pounds 79.1m) with Pounds 90m (Pounds 78m) from continuing
operations. Gearing at the year end was reduced to 26 per cent (46 per
cent).
Mr Ray Way, chairman, said the group's financial position continued to
strengthen and borrowings were 'well under control'.
The furniture division, Ian Walker Furniture, hit by sterling's realignment
last year, saw margins restored and sales increase to help push operating
profits in the consumer goods division up from Pounds 77,000 to Pounds 1.53m
on turnover of Pounds 38.9m (Pounds 33.3m).
International demand helped sales at Erlson Engineering, a supplier of
turbocharger components, increase by 18 per cent while hardening commodity
prices and better customer demand helped trading conditions in the aluminium
refining division. Total operating profits for the industrial goods division
rose from Pounds 4.59m to Pounds 4.71m on turnover of Pounds 43.1m (Pounds
37.8m).
Mr Way said diversification was essential in the precision engineering
division where margins continued to be under pressure and order intakes were
down because of cuts in defence expenditure. A programme was under way to
shift the customer base of Bellhouse Hartwell and BHW (Components) and
penetrate the civil sector.
A final dividend of 1.5p (1.2p) makes a 2p (1.6p) total. Earnings were 3.06p
(0.96p).
</TEXT>
