FT  15 JUL 94 / UK Company News: Marks and Spencer sales receive overseas
spur
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
First-quarter sales for Marks and Spencer, the retailer, in north America,
continental Europe and east Asia were up on last year and particularly good
in Hong Kong and the International Franchise Group, Sir Richard Greenbury,
chairman, told the annual meeting.
He added that sales in the UK were 'up to expectations'.
The group is to open two new stores, in Paris and Valencia, in the autumn
and is investigating the possibility of moving into Japan and China.
The pace of expansion in the UK was 'accelerating', said Sir Richard, with
plans for capital expenditure of more than Pounds 1bn over the next three
years. In the past year capital expenditure reached 'a new high of Pounds
350m.' the group had 'the biggest footage expansion programme in (its)
history'.
M&amp;S shares rose 8p to 414p.
