<HEADLINE>
FT  15 JUL 94 / Arts: Today's Television
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By CHRISTOPHER DUNKLEY
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
It was, of course, entirely predictable that if two series about sport and
health should suddenly turn up, the broadcasters would ensure that they
would clash head on so that those really interested would have to use the
VCR to record one or the other. Those involved in The Contenders on BBC1 at
7.00 include hurdler Sally Gunnell and cyclist Chris Boardman. Those
involved in Body Heat at 7.00 on ITV include Chris Boardman and Sally
Gunnell. The BBC programme is concerned today with the effect of diet upon
performance. The ITV programme is described as 'a competitive fitness
series'. BBC Proms 1994 begins on BBC2 and Radio 3 at 8.00 with Andrew Davis
conducting the BBC Symphony Orchestra, the BBC Singers, the Philharmonia
Chorus, and the BBC Symphony Chorus, all participating in Schoenberg's
cantata 'Gurrelieder'. The soloists include soprano Karita Mattila, mezzo
Ann Murray, and tenors Neil Breeden and Philip Langridge. For those who
prefer their culture less highbrow, Fancy A Bit celebrates the humour of the
seaside postcard (8.45 Radio 2).
