FT  15 JUL 94 / Dentists face health reforms
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ALAN PIKE
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Ways of extending the purchaser-provider structure of the 1991 health
reforms to the dental service are being considered by the government, Alan
Pike writes.
A green paper published yesterday envisages introducing a system under which
health authorities would purchase dental services at local level. They would
agree contracts with dentists to obtain services reflecting specific local
conditions and the state of oral health in the area.
Dr Brian Mawhinney, health minister, said: 'The government believes that
there would be clear advantages if the system of payment for dentists could
be made more sensitive to local needs and priorities for dental care. That
was the thrust of our changes to the wider NHS, and the benefits there are
now tangible.'
