<TEXT>
Mr Bob Horton, chairman of Railtrack, last night condemned the RMT transport
union for 'irresponsible scaremongering' over safety standards on the rail
network during the one-day strikes, Robert Taylor writes.
Speaking as the RMT executive met to discuss its planned move to escalate
the signalling staff dispute which has shut down most of Britain's rail
network over the past five Wednesdays, Mr Horton accused it of 'trying to
bring the country to a halt by frightening the public into staying at home'.
